The paper deals with subspace codes and their list decoding, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The handling of insertions and deletions in subspace codes involves linear algebraic techniques, which could place the paper in the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
